Uhuru suspends schools’ co-curricular activities like sports, drama, music and prize-giving for 90 days.Teachers seek ways of juggling between Covid-19 protocols and talent development. Officials of the Kenya Secondary Schools Sports Association (KSSSA) are planning to hold a meeting with Education Cabinet Secretary George Magoha to salvage the battered schools sports programmes after the government put them on hold for a further three months in Covid-19 containment measures. 

Peter Orero, the KSSSA chairman, Sunday said while they would not, and cannot, challenge a presidential directive, they will hold a meeting with the Education Cabinet Secretary to give their views on how the school sports programmes could be salvaged. 



