Orero argued that through sports activities, the immunity of children is boosted and it’s, therefore, the best way to prevent the spread of the coronavirus disease. 

“We have realised that since the form four classes resumed last year, no student has died and we believe no student will die because of coronavirus,” Orero said, adding that those who are vulnerable are the teachers and support staff that will need to be taken care off. 



